sVnews
p4
VIn a span of three days, two vocal recitals were held at  Kalabharathi.  Noted vocalist M. Jalajakshi for Visakha Music and Dance Academy performed first . She was  accompanied on violin by her son, M.S.N. Murty who is also a reputed vocalist, along with noted mridangam player Mangalagiri Sridhar. She began  withSurati Varnamfollowed bySrimahaganapathim.She mainly sangManavi Aalakincharadate(Nalinikanthi) withswaram. Srinivas and Sridhar, both while accompanying and in their turns, expertly turned out to be her piers. Her performance kept all glued to their seats.C. Gurucharan from Chennai performed on Saturday. It was organised by Visakha Music Academy.  Komanduri V. Krishna on violin and virtuoso V.V. Ramanamurty&#8217;s performance on mridangam was laudable. This was followed by an exquisiteaalapanaofAandolikaandtaanamfor singing pallavi.He concluded withswaraminRaagamalikainKarnaranjani,NalinikanthiandVarali.
